, "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2017-12-17T01:11:16Z", "updated_at": "2020-11-05T11:50:33Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\nMany online data hosting portals (zenodo, figshare, dataverse?) seems to not support datasets to have full hierarchy of directories, and provide only a \"flat list\" structure.  To avoid uploading 1 huge tarball, many datasets (e.g. [dataverse1](https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=doi:10.7910/DVN/I7KP3V)) then are uploaded e.g. with each subject being a separate tarball.  In turn, we could export all top level files individually while uploading sub-directories as tarballs. This would be especially useful for incremental uploads where any particular subdataset is updated and remote hosting providing allowing for versioning of the files (e.g. figshare, dataverse)", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2038/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2038/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}